In [102]:
def statistics(data):
    #calculate the statistics of sum, mean, standard deviation, skewness, kurtosis
    Sum_v = np.sum(data)
    Mean_v = np.mean(data)
    Standard_deviation_v = np.std(data)
    skew_v = skew(data)
    Kurtosis_v = kurtosis(data)
    
    #store the summary statistics in a dictionary
    summary = {
        "Sum": Sum_v,
        "Mean":Mean_v,
        "Standard_Deviation": Standard_deviation_v,
        "Skewness": skew_v,
        "Kurtosis": Kurtosis_v
    }
    
    return summary

# calling the method
data = df['remote_ratio']
result = statistics(data)

# print the statistics
print("Summary statistics are")
for key, value in result.items():
    print(key + ":", value)
